Status of This Document {#status}
==================================

<em>This section describes the status of this document at the time of its publication.</em>

This is a work in progress and is subject to change. This document is maintained by the HKIR Development Team and is intended to serve as a reference for standardized data modeling practices.

Introduction {#intro}
=====================

This specification defines a comprehensive data model for structuring and organizing data in a standardized format. The data model provides a foundation for consistent data representation, validation, and exchange across different systems and applications.

## Purpose and Scope ## {#purpose}

This data model aims to:

* Provide a clear and consistent structure for data representation
* Enable interoperability between different systems
* Support extensibility for future enhancements
* Facilitate data validation and quality assurance

Key Concepts {#concepts}
========================

This section introduces the fundamental concepts that form the basis of the data model.

## Core Principles ## {#principles}

The data model is built on the following core principles:

* **Consistency**: Data structures follow consistent patterns and naming conventions
* **Extensibility**: The model can be extended to accommodate new requirements
* **Interoperability**: Data can be exchanged between different systems
* **Validation**: Data structures include validation rules to ensure data quality

## Terminology ## {#terminology}

<dfn export>Entity</dfn>
: A discrete unit of data with defined attributes and relationships

<dfn export>Attribute</dfn>
: A property or characteristic of an entity

<dfn export>Relationship</dfn>
: A connection or association between two or more entities

Data Model {#data-model}
=========================

This section defines the core data structures and their relationships.

## Entity Structure ## {#entity-structure}

Each entity in the data model consists of:

* A unique identifier
* A set of attributes that describe the entity
* Optional relationships to other entities

## Data Types ## {#data-types}

The data model supports the following data types:

* **String**: Text data
* **Number**: Numeric data (integers and floating-point)
* **Boolean**: True/false values
* **Date**: Temporal data
* **Array**: Ordered collections of values
* **Object**: Structured data with nested attributes

## Validation Rules ## {#validation}

Data validation ensures that:

* Required attributes are present
* Data types are correct
* Values fall within acceptable ranges
* Relationships reference valid entities
